#: src/config.md:1
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr "組態"

#: src/config.md:3
msgid "Configuration format"
msgstr "組態格式"

#: src/config.md:5
msgid ""
"You can configure maturin in `tool.maturin` section of [`pyproject.toml`]"
"(https://peps.python.org/pep-0518/#tool-table)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:7
msgid "Configuration keys"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:9
msgid "Cargo options"
msgstr "Cargo 選項"

#: src/config.md:11
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin]\n"
"# Build artifacts with the specified Cargo profile\n"
"profile = \"release\"\n"
"# List of features to activate\n"
"features = [\"foo\", \"bar\"]\n"
"# Activate all available features\n"
"all-features = false\n"
"# Do not activate the `default` feature\n"
"no-default-features = false\n"
"# Cargo manifest path\n"
"manifest-path = \"Cargo.toml\"\n"
"# Require Cargo.lock and cache are up to date\n"
"frozen = false\n"
"# Require Cargo.lock is up to date\n"
"locked = false\n"
"# Override a configuration value (unstable)\n"
"config = []\n"
"# Unstable (nightly-only) flags to Cargo, see 'cargo -Z help' for details\n"
"unstable-flags = []\n"
"# Extra arguments that will be passed to rustc as `cargo rustc [...] -- "
"[...] [arg1] [arg2]`\n"
"rustc-args = []\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:35
msgid ""
"These are `cargo` build options, refer Cargo documentation [here](https://"
"doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/commands/cargo-rustc.html)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:37
msgid "maturin options"
msgstr "maturin 選項"

#: src/config.md:39
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin]\n"
"# Include additional files\n"
"include = []\n"
"# Exclude files\n"
"exclude = []\n"
"# Bindings type\n"
"bindings = \"pyo3\"\n"
"# Control the platform tag on linux\n"
"compatibility = \"manylinux2014\"\n"
"# Don't check for manylinux compliance\n"
"skip-auditwheel = false\n"
"# Python source directory\n"
"python-source = \"src\"\n"
"# Python packages to include\n"
"python-packages = [\"foo\", \"bar\"]\n"
"# Strip the library for minimum file size\n"
"strip = true\n"
"# Source distribution generator,\n"
"# supports cargo (default) and git.\n"
"sdist-generator = \"cargo\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:62
msgid ""
"The `[tool.maturin.include]` and `[tool.maturin.exclude]` configuration are "
"inspired by [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs/pyproject/#include-and-"
"exclude)."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:66
msgid "To specify files or globs directly:"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:68
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\"path/**/*\", \"some/other/file\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\"path/**/*\", \"some/other/file\"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:72
msgid "To specify a specific target format (`sdist` or `wheel`):"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:74
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"path/**/*\", format = \"sdist\" },\n"
"  { path = \"all\", format = [\"sdist\", \"wheel\"] },\n"
"  { path = \"for/wheel/**/*\", format = \"wheel\" }\n"
"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""
"```toml\n"
"include = [\n"
"  { path = \"path/**/*\", format = \"sdist\" },\n"
"  { path = \"all\", format = [\"sdist\", \"wheel\"] },\n"
"  { path = \"for/wheel/**/*\", format = \"wheel\" }\n"
"]\n"
"```"

#: src/config.md:82
msgid ""
"The default behavior is apply these configurations to both `sdist` and "
"`wheel` targets."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:85
msgid "target specific maturin options"
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:87
msgid ""
"Currently only macOS deployment target SDK version can be configured for "
"`x86_64-apple-darwin` and `aarch64-apple-darwin` targets, other targets have "
"no options yet."
msgstr ""

#: src/config.md:91
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[tool.maturin.target.<triple>]\n"
"# macOS deployment target SDK version\n"
"macos-deployment-target = \"11.0\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

