"This structure is recommended to avoid [a common `ImportError` pitfall]"
"(https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/issues/490)"
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:178
msgid ""
"maturin will add the native extension as a module in your python folder. "
"When using develop, maturin will copy the native library and for cffi also "
"the glue code to your python folder. You should add those files to your "
"gitignore."
msgstr ""

#: src/index.md:180
msgid ""
"With cffi you can do `from .my_project import lib` and then use `lib."
"my_native_function`, with pyo3/rust-cpython you can directly `from ."
"my_project import my_native_function`."
