#: src/tutorial.md:190
msgid "Build and install the module with `maturin develop`"
msgstr ""

#: src/tutorial.md:192
msgid ""
"Note that _this is just a Rust project_ at this point, and with few "
"exceptions you can build it as you'd expect using `cargo build`. maturin "
"helps with this, however, adding some platform-specific build configuration "
"and ultimately packaging the binary results as a wheel (a `.whl` file, which "
"is an archive of compiled components suitable for installation with `pip`, "
"the Python package manager)."
